# init(int64s:)

**Initializer**

Creates a sequence of integers from an array of numbers.

## Declaration

```swift
convenience init(int64s int64Values: [NSNumber])
```

## Parameters

- **int64Values**: An array of integer values represented as [doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/Foundation/NSNumber] instances.

## Creating a sequence

- **init(strings:)**: Creates a sequence of strings from a string array.
- **init(empty:)**: Creates an empty sequence of strings or integers.
